.TH "TEMPLATE" 7 "February 2026" "atomdns handlers" "atomdns authors"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fItemplate\fP \- use Go templates to reply

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The \fItemplate\fP handler allows you to dynamically respond to queries by just writing a Go template. The
template is a file that is watched and reloaded when it changes. The template is the string version of a message
is generated by \fB\fCcodeberg.org/miekg/dns\fR, i.e.:

.PP
.RS

.nf
;; QUERY, rcode: NOERROR, id: 49123, flags: qr rd ra

;; QUESTION SECTION:
miek.nl.                IN      MX

;; ANSWER SECTION:
miek.nl.        11381   IN      MX      10 aspmx2.googlemail.com.
miek.nl.        11381   IN      MX      10 aspmx3.googlemail.com.
miek.nl.        11381   IN      MX      5 alt1.aspmx.l.google.com.
miek.nl.        11381   IN      MX      5 alt2.aspmx.l.google.com.
miek.nl.        11381   IN      MX      1 aspmx.l.google.com.

.fi
.RE

.PP
This is a \fIvalid\fP template and will be parsed by \fItemplate\fP into a message and returned to the client.
However, for one thing, the query ID will not be correct, so that line should become:

.PP
.RS

.nf
;; QUERY, rcode: NOERROR, id: {{.ID}}, flags: qr rd ra

.fi
.RE

.PP
When nothing is matched \fItemplate\fP will call the next handler, see below for more details.

.SH "SYNTAX"
.PP
.RS

.nf
template REGEX [TYPE]... {
    TEMPLATE
}

.fi
.RE

.IP \(bu 4
\fBREGEX\fP will be matched against the incoming question name. Expressions larger than a 1000 charactes
return an error during setup.
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTYPE\fP is the type to be matched, if not given all types are matched.
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTEMPLATE\fP is that template file that should be parsed and executed. If that the path is relative the
global \fB\fCroot\fR path is prepended.


.SH "TEMPLATES"
.PP
A template must return a complete message that can be parsed back into an actual DNS message. The template
parsing is \fInot\fP case insensitive, i.e. \fB\fCanswer section:\fR will not be parsed but \fB\fCANSWER SECTION:\fR is.

.PP
Each template gets the following variables (see the godoc of Data):

.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Zone\fR the matched zone string (e.g. \fB\fCexample.org.\fR), from the context.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.ID\fR the query ID.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Name\fR the query name.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Class\fR the query class.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Type\fR the query type.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Question\fR the matched question RR.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.Msg\fR the complete message.
.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fC.ResponseWriter\fR that holds all the data that can be extracted from the response writer.


.PP
And the following functions (all functions start with a capital letter):

.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fCCtx(key string)\fR return the value for the key from the current context. This allows extracting any data
other handlers have added to the context, such as the \fIgeoip\fP handler does, i.e. with \fB\fCCtx("geoip/city")\fR.


.SH "EXAMPLES"
.SH "RESOLVE TO NXDOMAIN"
.PP
.RS

.nf
example.org. {
    template .* {
      nxdomain.go.tmpl
    }
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
Where \fB\fCnxdomain.go.tmpl\fR contains:

.PP
.RS

.nf
;; QUERY, rcode: NOERROR, id: {{.ID}}, flags: qr rd ra

;; QUESTION SECTION:
{{.Question}}

;; AUTHORITY SECTION:
{{.Zone}}   IN SOA ns.icann.org. noc.dns.icann.org. 2025082229 7200 3600 1209600 3600
{{if Ctx "geoip/asn"}}
{{.Zone}}   IN TXT "{{Ctx "geoip/asn"}}"
{{end}}

.fi
.RE

.SH "ALSO SEE"
.PP
Go regexp
\[la]https://golang.org/pkg/regexp/\[ra] for details about the regex implementation and
Go template
\[la]https://golang.org/pkg/text/template/\[ra] for the template language reference. And atomdns\-geoip(7)
for documentation on what elements are added to the context.

.SH "BUGS"
.PP
The template is parsed on every query, which is a bit excessive. See https://codeberg.org/miekg/dns/issues/319
\[la]https://codeberg.org/miekg/dns/issues/319\[ra].
